Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 17 (XINHUA) -- China is expected to 
hold a securities and futures fair here in late April this year. 
  The fair, the first of its kind in China, will be sponsored 
jointly by the Ministry of Finance, the newspaper "CHINA 
SECURITIES", the Beijing Commodity Exchange, China International 
Futures Brokers Ltd, and several other Beijing-based agencies 
and companies. 
  It aims to spread knowledge of securities and futures and 
the 
achievements in the development of the joint stock system, and 
to promote the issuing of treasury bonds. 

